"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The set_style() function in seaborn is used to set the aesthetic style of the plots, but it does not accept the rc parameter for overriding matplotlib parameters. The rc parameter should only be used with set_context() or set_theme(). Therefore, the code incorrectly uses set_style() with the rc argument.\", \"patch\": \"14c14\\n< sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n> sns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n\"}"